props.name: appTitle
props.docs: The title of your about screen.

props.name: copyright
props.docs: The copyright you would like to display.

props.name: domain
props.docs: The domain you want to display.  If set to `ecostruxure`, it renders an EcoStruxure icon.

props.name: imageUrl
props.docs: Sets the background image for your about page.

props.name: version
props.docs: The version number you want to display.

props.name: option
props.docs:
Define the type of application. updating the option will impact the font used.
- `technical`: For technical application (i.e. EcoStuxure), the font used will be `Nunito`.
- `website` or `dcx`: For `se.com` application, the font used will be `Arial Rounded`.

props.name: appTitle
props.docs: The title of your authentication screen.

props.name: copyright
props.docs: The copyright you would like to display.

props.name: domain
props.docs: The domain you want to display.  If set to `ecostruxure`, it renders an EcoStruxure icon.

props.name: hide
props.docs: If set to `true`, this will hide the authentication screen.

props.name: imageUrl
props.docs: Sets the background image for your authentication screen.

props.name: version
props.docs: The version number you want to display.

props.name: duration
props.docs:
Set the duration (in ms) that the banner will automatically switch slides.
Default is `6000`.

props.name: active
props.docs: Indicates the active banner item in your banner component.

props.name: imageUrl
props.docs: Sets the background image for your banner item.

events.docs: Send an event when the banner item changes

props.name: clickable
props.docs:
Defines the se-block item's ability to appear clickable / selectable.
Default setting is `false`, resulting in no hover effects on the block level.
`true` adds a hover effect on the se-block. The cursor will change to `pointer`, a box-shadow will appear, and a `$se-life-green` bar will appear at the top of the block.

props.name: clickableBar
props.docs:
Defines clickable se-block item's bar on hover.
Default setting is `false`.
`true` renders a `$se-life-green` colored bar on a hover.

props.name: color
props.docs:
Optional property that defines the background color of the block.
Default setting is `alternative`, rendering the "alternative" theme background.
`none` has no background.
`standard` renders the "standard" theme background.

props.name: corner
props.docs:
Defines the se-block corner radius.
Default setting is `small`, rendering a rounded, 4px rounded corner.
`none` is for a sharp, 90 degree corner.
`nano` is for a slightly rounded, 2px rounded corner.

props.name: display
props.docs:
Defines how to display the element.
`flex` is the default display.
`block` helps in specific cases. Make sure you know what you are doing.

props.name: divider
props.docs:
Defines whether or not a divider will be applied to the se-block header and footer.
`true` will add a divider to the se-block-header and se-block-footer, if they are present.
`false` will remove dividers on the se-block header and se-block-footer, if they are present.

props.name: enlarged
props.docs:
When the display is set to `grid`, this property determines if the block should have double the width and height of a standard grid item.
Default setting is `false`, spanning 1 row and 1 column (1/1).
`true` spans 2 rows and 2 columns (2/2).
`vertical` spans 2 rows (2/1).
`horizontal` spans 2 columns (1/2).

props.name: height
props.docs: Defines the specific height of a block.  Useful to create easy layouts under `se-container` which uses `flex` by default.

props.name: loading
props.docs: Displays the loading icon if set to `true`.  Default setting is `false`.

props.name: margin
props.docs:
Defines the spacing around the outside edge of a block.
Default `none` is 0px.
`small` is 4px.
`medium` is 8px.
`large` is 16px.
`xlarge` is 32px.

props.name: option
props.docs:
Defines the visual appearance of a block.
Default setting is `basic`, which will remove any spacing.
`widget` will create a flat widget look and feel with a `medium` margin around it.
`card` will create a card look and feel with rounded corners, and with a `large` margin around it.
Pending deprecation - `card-old` follows a prior design pattern with a box-shadow and will be deprecated.

props.name: outline
props.docs:
Defines the se-block outline.
Default setting is `false`.
Setting this property to `true` will add a 1px border.

props.name: outlineColor
props.docs:
Defines the se-block outline color.
Default setting is `standard`, which renders the outline with the `$se-super-light-grey` color.
`primary` defines the outline color as `$se-life-green`, used primarily for technical applications when the block is selected.
`secondary` defines the outline color as `$se-sky-blue`.

props.name: width
props.docs: Defines the specific width of a block.  Useful to create easy layouts under `se-container` which uses `flex` by default.

props.name: option
props.docs:
The block-content component will add 8px padding on the top and bottom, and 16px padding on the left and right by default.
When the option is set to `fill`, the content will fill the whole space of the block-content with no padding.

| Slot   | Description                                                                                       |

components.docs:
| Slot   | Description                                                                                       |
| ------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `icon` | Another way to configure your own icon instead of using the icon property (used to load svg icon) |
| none   | The text of the button                                                                            |

props.name: block
props.docs:
Optional property that defines if the button displays as a block in it's container.
When set to true, the button will be as wide as its container.

props.name: caption
props.docs: Optional property that defines if the button has a caption or tooltip text.

props.name: color
props.docs: Defines the background color of the button. The default setting is `standard`.

props.name: disabled
props.docs: Optional property that defines if the button is disabled.  Set to `false` by default.

props.name: icon
props.docs: Optional property that determines if your button includes an icon.

props.name: iconColor
props.docs: Optional property to change the color of the icon when needed. For example, the user dropdown in the header component.

props.name: iconOnly
props.docs: Property to specify if the button should only display an icon (no extra spacing).

props.name: option
props.docs:
Defines the visual appearance of the button.
`flat` is the default option, which includes a gray background.
`raised` adds a box shadow to the button.
`outline` adds a border to the button.
`login` and `signup` are specific options for "Login" and "Sign Up" buttons in your application.

props.name: selected
props.docs: Optional property that defines if the button should be shown as selected. Used with the `se-radio-group` component.

props.name: size
props.docs:
Defines the size of the button.
`nano` sets the font to 12px font and a 24px height.  Used primarily with the `se-radio-group` component.
`small` is the default option, with a 14px font and a 32px height.
`medium` sets the font to 16px and the height to 40px.
`large` sets the font to 18px and the height to 48px.

props.name: type
props.docs:
Optional property.
`button`	is the default setting, creating a clickable button.
`submit`	creates a "submit" button (useful to submit form-data).
`reset`	creates a reset button (useful to reset form-data to its initial values).

props.name: value
props.docs: Optional property that defines the value of your button, which gets passed to the parent component when clicking the button.

methods.name: setDisabled
methods.docs: Sets the disabled property for your button from the parent component.

methods.name: setGrouped
methods.docs: Indicates if the button is part of a group of buttons within the `se-radio-group` component.

events.docs: Passes button data to the parent component on a click.

props.name: background
props.docs:
Defines the color schema of the checkbox when the option is set to `onoff`.
The default value is `standard`.

props.name: color
props.docs:
Defines the color of the checkbox for when the option is set to `checkbox` or `switch`.
The default value is `success`, rendering a green color.
The `secondary` setting renders a blue color.

props.name: disabled
props.docs: Optional property that defines if the checkbox is disabled.  Set to `false` by default.

props.name: header
props.docs:
Reduces the visual height of the checkbox when the option is set to `onoff`.
Useful if the on/off checkbox is within a header element.

props.name: label
props.docs: The label of the checkbox that will be attached to the box.

props.name: labelPos
props.docs:
Sets the position of the label for your checkbox component.
The default setting is `right` when the option is set to `checkbox`.
The default setting is `left` when the option is set to `switch`.

props.name: option
props.docs:
Determines the visual appearance of the component.
`checkbox` is the default option, which will render the component like a standard HTML checkbox.
`switch` renders the component like a toggle switch.
`onoff` renders the component like an "on/off" switch, with a red "off" button and a green "on" button.

props.name: required
props.docs: Adds a red asterisk if the checkbox is required when used in a form field.  Default is `false`.

props.name: selected
props.docs: The "checked" state of the checkbox, `false` by default.

props.name: textOff
props.docs: Defines the text the user will see for the "off" or "inactive" part of the checkbox when option is set to `onoff`.  Set to `OFF` by default.

props.name: textOn
props.docs: Defines the text the user will see for the "on" or "active" part of the checkbox when option is set to `onoff`.  Set to `ON` by default.

props.name: value
props.docs: The value you want to pass to the parent component when the checkbox is checked.

methods.name: setRequired
methods.docs: Sets the required property on the checkbox element.  Used when the checkbox is within a form field.

events.docs: Send the checkbox value to the parent component when clicking on the checkbox.

props.name: block
props.docs:
Optional property that defines if the chip displays as a block in it's container.
When set to true, the chip will be as wide as its container.

props.name: canClose
props.docs: Indicates whether or not the chip has a close button.  Set to `false` by default.

props.name: color
props.docs: Defines the background color of the chip.  The default setting is `standard`, which is a light gray color.

props.name: disabled
props.docs: Indicates whether or not the chip is disabled.  Set to `false` by default.

props.name: selected
props.docs: Indicates whether or not the chip is selected.  Set to `false` by default.

props.name: size
props.docs:
Defines the size of the chip.
`nano` sets the font to 14px and the height to 24px.
`small` is the default option, with a 16px font and a 32px height.

props.name: value
props.docs: The text you want to display in your chip.

events.docs: Send the chip value to the parent component when clicking the close button of a chip.

props.name: color
props.docs:
Defines the background color of the container.
`none` has no background.
`standard` is `se-background`, light gray.
`alternative` is a white background.

props.name: columnSize
props.docs:
When in `display="grid"`, defines the mininimum width of a column. It automatically figures out the appropriate number of columns from there.
Default is `350px`.

props.name: direction
props.docs:
Defines the direction of the flex element.
`row` is the default direction. This is perfect to use with flex content.
`column` is useful in specific cases. Make sure you know what you are doing.

props.name: display
props.docs:
Defines how to display the element.
`flex` is the default display.
`block` will set each container to be as large and high as it's content. Selecting this display will automatically configure each child element to have "display: block".

props.name: option
props.docs:
Defines the inner appearance of a container.
`fill` is the default option, taking the full space of the container. This option automatically sets the color property to `standard` (gray) if color has not been set.
`widget` adds a `small` padding around the container to equally space all child elements. This option automatically sets the color property to `standard` (gray) if color has not been set.
`centered` centers the container so the content does not exceed a maximum width.
`card` adds a `medium` padding around each child element.  This option automatically sets the color property to `alternative` (white) if color has not been set.
Pending deprecation - `card-old` follows a prior design pattern with a box-shadow and will be deprecated.
`inherited` will insure that no specific style is applied to the container.

props.name: padding
props.docs:
Defines the spacing around the inside edge of a container.
`none` is 0px.
`small` is 4px.
`medium` is 8px.
`large` is 16px.
`xlarge` is 32px.

props.name: position
props.docs:
In specific cases, it may be necessary to define the container with an absolute position (such as inside an angular router-container). Most of the time, the default position will work perfectly with CSS flex box.
`relative` is the default position. This is perfect to use with flex content.
`absolute` is useful in specific cases. Make sure you know what you are doing.

props.name: rowSize
props.docs: When in `display="grid"`, defines the height of each container.  Default is `300px`.

props.name: canBackdrop
props.docs: Option to enable clicking on the dialog's backdrop. Will automatically close the modal.  Default setting is `true`.

props.name: color
props.docs:
Defines the color of the dialog header.
`alternative`: Alternative background with primary color for the text
`primary`: Primary color schema and default setting.

props.name: open
props.docs: Indicates whether or not the dialog is open or closed.  Default setting is `false`.

props.name: size
props.docs:
Defines the size of the modal.
`small`: used in alerts and messages
`medium`: default setting, used by other apps
`fill`: takes the full space of the screen

methods.name: backdropClicked
methods.docs: Emit the `backdrop` event from the dialog's parent component if `canBackdrop=true`. When the event is emitted, the dialog is automatically closed.

events.docs: Send data to the parent component when the backdrop is clicked.

Send data to the parent component when clicking an element within the dialog to close it.
The modal can then be safely removed from the DOM.

| `trigger` | Corresponds to the trigger element to open the dropdown (`se-icon`, `se-button` ...) |

props.name: alignment
props.docs:
Defines how to align the dropdown container.
`right`: Position the container with respect to the right side of the trigger element.
`left`: Position the container with respect to the left side of the trigger element.

props.name: maxHeight
props.docs: Sets the maximum height of the dropdown.  Default setting is "400px".

props.name: maxWidth
props.docs: Sets the maximum width of the dropdown.  Default setting is "200px".

props.name: verticalAlignment
props.docs:
Defines how to vertically align the dropdown container.
`top`: Position the container with respect to the top side of the trigger element.
`bottom`: Position the container with respect to the bottom side of the trigger element.

methods.name: close
methods.docs: Method to close the dropdown from outside its parent element.

methods.name: open
methods.docs: Method to open the dropdown from outside its parent element.

events.docs: Event emitted when the dropdown has been touched. Every dropdown listen to this event to avoid avoid multiple dropdown open at the same time.
Event emitted when the dropdown has been closed.
Event emitted when the dropdown has been opened.

props.name: color
props.docs:
Indicates the color of your main action button .
The Default setting is `primary`, rendering a green background.
The `alternative` setting renders a white background.

props.name: icon
props.docs: Property that determines if an icon is included in the main action button.

props.name: option
props.docs:
Property that determines the functionality of the FAB.
The default setting is `speeddial`, which will show/hide a dropdown menu when clicking on the FAB.
The `backtotop` setting returns you to the top of the page you are viewing when clicking on the FAB.

props.name: position
props.docs:
Property that determines the position of the component.
The default setting is `bottom`, rendering a FAB at the bottom right corner.
The `top` setting renders the FAB at the top right corner.

methods.name: toggleAction
methods.docs: Use this method to toggle (show/hide) the mini action buttons.

props.name: icon
props.docs: Property that determines if an icon is included in the floating action button.

events.docs: Send the value of the caption to the parent when clicking on the item.

props.name: block
props.docs:
Optional property that defines if the field displays as a block in it's container.
When set to true, the field will be as wide as its container.
both field label auto adjust when it set to inline

props.name: disabled
props.docs: Optional property that defines if the form field is disabled.  Set to `false` by default.

props.name: label
props.docs: Defines the text value of the label in your form field.

props.name: labelWidth
props.docs: Optional property to define the proportion of the label width. The content (input) will take the rest of if. Defaulted to 40%

props.name: option
props.docs:
Defines the layout of your form field.
`inline` is the default option, and is always applied if the type is set to `checkbox`.  This sets the input or select field adjacent to the label.
`stacked` option will render the input or select field below the label.

props.name: padding
props.docs:
Defines the spacing around the inside edge of a container.
`none` is 0px.
`small` is 4px.
`medium` is 8px.

props.name: required
props.docs:
Determines if the input is required by the application.
Set to `false` by default.
Setting this value to `true` will render a red asterisk next to your label.

props.name: status
props.docs: Sets a red border on an input field if there's an error, an orange border if there's a warning, and a green border if a successful input.

props.name: type
props.docs:
Defines whether the form field's input is a text field (`input`), a checkbox (`checkbox`), a radio button (`radio`), or a dropdown menu (`select`).
`input` is the default type.

props.name: value
props.docs:
Defines the value of your form field to get passed to the parent component.
When the type is set to "input", this value will be the default placeholder in your input field.

events.docs: Passes form data to the parent component on a click (`checkbox` or `radio`), menu change (`select`), or when the input field loses focus.

props.name: actionText
props.docs: Defines the text you want your custom action button to read.

props.name: canClose
props.docs:
Displays a "button" to close the snackbar.
The default setting is `false`.
This will be visible if set to `true`.

props.name: duration
props.docs:
Indicates the duration (in milliseconds) that the snackbar will display on screen before auto-closing, if `canClose` is set to false.
The default setting is 5000.

props.name: icon
props.docs: The name of the icon you wish to display.  The default icon is an information circle.

props.name: message
props.docs: The content of the message you want the snackbar to display.

props.name: open
props.docs: Indicates if the snackbar is open.  Set to `false` (closed) by default.

props.name: type
props.docs:
Indicates the background color of your snackbar.
`success`: green
`warning`: orange
`error`: red
`information`: dark grey, default setting

events.docs: Sends information to the parent component when clicking a custom action button.
Sends information to the parent component when closing the snackbar.

props.name: color
props.docs:
Sets the background color of your stepper.
The default setting is `primary`, implementing a green background for the stepper visual items.
The `alternative` setting implements a white background for the stepper visual items.  This setting is best used against a gray background.

props.name: linear
props.docs:
Defines if the stepper items must be completed sequentially.
The default setting is `true`, each stepper item must be validated before advancing to the next step.
`false` allows each step to be selected in any order.

methods.name: next
methods.docs:
Call the `next` method to navigate to the next step from the step that is currently selected.
This will not work in linear mode if the next step is not validated.

methods.name: previous
methods.docs: Call the `previous` method to navigate to the previous step from the step that is currently selected.

methods.name: reset
methods.docs:
Call the `reset` method to reset the stepper to the indicated step.  This also invalidates any validated steps.
It no step parameter is provided, it will reset to the first stepper item.

props.name: active
props.docs: Indicates the content for the currently selected step in the stepper.

props.name: label
props.docs: Indicates the label for your stepper item.

props.name: validated
props.docs:
Indicates whether a required item's data has been validated.  Useful if using a form field.
When the stepper component is set to linear mode, all stepper items will need to be validated before advancing the stpper.

events.docs:
Event to send to the parent component when a stepper item's data is validated.
The boolean validated property is passed to the parent.

# se-tabbar

| Slot    | Description                                                                                                                  |
| ------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| none    | Slot with no name will be positioned to the start of the element (left)                                                      |
| `start` | Positions to the `left` of the content. The start element will be darker than the rest of the element                        |
| `end`   | Positions to the `right` of the content.                                                                                     |
| `edge`  | Positions to the `right` of the content after the `end` slot to be used behind a darker background. Used for Search section. |

props.name: color
props.docs:
Indicates the color of your tab bar.
Default setting is `primary`, rendering a green background for nav-bars and ultra-light-grey-1 for content.
The `alternative` setting renders a white background.

props.name: option
props.docs:
Defines the function of the tabbar.
Default `nav` creates a tab bar that functions as a nav-bar.
`content` creates a ta bbar that functions as a content section tab bar.

props.name: overflow
props.docs:
Indicates the overflow behavior of your tab bar.
Default setting is `scroll`, keeping all tabs in one horizontal row.
The `stack` setting allows your tabbar content wrap to new lines.
The `compact` setting allows your tabbar content to scroll, but all stack the text together as much as possible.

Optional property that provides the arrow icon based on which string is provided, and also causes the `clickable` property to `true`.
`asc` defines the icon as an upwards arrow in black.
`desc` defines the icon as a downwards arrow in black.

The default setting is `hover`, triggering the tooltip when hovering over the parent element.
The `click` action triggers the tooltip when you click on the parent element.

props.name: position
props.docs:
Indicates the position of your tooltip.
The default setting is `bottom`, rendering the tooltip below its parent.

methods.name: close
methods.docs: Method to close the tooltip separate from hovering or clicking the parent element.

methods.name: open
methods.docs: Method to open the tooltip separate from hovering or clicking the parent element.

events.docs: Closes the tooltip when another tooltip is opened.
Event emitted when the tooltip has been closed.
Event emitted when the tooltip has been opened.
